WEBVTT

00:51.177 --> 00:54.388
<i>♪ When I was small
I believed in Santa Claus ♪</i>

00:54.388 --> 00:56.682
<i>♪ Though I knew it was my dad ♪</i>

00:57.433 --> 01:00.436
<i>♪ And I would hang up
My stocking at Christmas ♪</i>

01:00.436 --> 01:02.897
<i>♪ Open my presents
And I'd be glad ♪</i>

01:03.731 --> 01:06.609
<i>♪ But the last time I played
Father Christmas ♪</i>

01:06.609 --> 01:08.861
<i>♪ I stood outside
A department store ♪</i>

01:10.029 --> 01:12.948
<i>♪ A gang of kids came over
And mugged me ♪</i>

01:12.948 --> 01:15.326
<i>♪ And knocked my reindeer
To the floor ♪</i>

01:16.869 --> 01:20.748
<i>♪ They said Father Christmas
Give us some money ♪</i>

01:20.748 --> 01:23.667
<i>♪ Don't mess around
With those silly toys ♪</i>

01:23.667 --> 01:26.420
<i>♪ We'll beat you up
If you don't hand it over ♪</i>

01:27.129 --> 01:29.840
<i>♪ We want your bread
So don't make us annoyed ♪</i>

01:30.382 --> 01:32.051
<i>♪ Give all the toys ♪</i>

01:32.843 --> 01:35.095
<i>♪ To the little rich boys ♪</i>

01:38.682 --> 01:41.352
<i>♪ Father Christmas
Give us some money ♪</i>

01:41.977 --> 01:44.772
<i>♪ Don't mess around
With those silly toys ♪</i>

01:44.772 --> 01:47.566
<i>♪ We'll beat you up
If you don't hand it over ♪</i>

01:48.192 --> 01:51.362
<i>♪ We want your bread
So don't make us annoyed ♪</i>

01:51.362 --> 01:52.905
<i>♪ Give all the toys ♪</i>

01:53.781 --> 01:55.908
<i>♪ To the little rich boys ♪</i>

02:23.352 --> 02:25.521
Master Wayne, come along now.

02:25.521 --> 02:27.857
Time for your cookie-wookies
before bedtime.

02:27.857 --> 02:29.817
Not yet, Alfred.

02:29.817 --> 02:30.985
Selina stole priceless art

02:30.985 --> 02:32.820
- from the Gotham City Museum.

02:32.820 --> 02:34.822
I must have justice.

02:38.242 --> 02:39.827
- Ha!

02:43.414 --> 02:45.541
Phew! Close one, huh, Alfred?

02:45.541 --> 02:47.001
Close indeed.

02:47.001 --> 02:49.044
Now, let's end this madcappery

02:49.044 --> 02:50.588
before you actually
do break...

02:51.922 --> 02:54.675
...something like your great
grandfather's ashes.

02:54.675 --> 02:56.760
- And that priceless Picasso.

03:04.184 --> 03:05.769
There's no way to run, Selina.

03:16.113 --> 03:17.072
Ah-ha!

03:21.744 --> 03:23.996
Young man, may I remind you

03:23.996 --> 03:26.707
that Christmas is a mere
two days away?

03:26.707 --> 03:29.084
Father Christmas is watching.

03:29.084 --> 03:32.630
Good! 'Cause even Santa
wouldn't wanna miss this.

03:34.006 --> 03:35.382
- Ha!

03:38.719 --> 03:39.720
Whoa!

03:40.554 --> 03:41.472
Master Wayne.

03:42.765 --> 03:44.683
Will you be sleeping
down there again?

03:48.103 --> 03:48.938
Whoa!

03:55.611 --> 03:56.612
Whoa!

03:57.863 --> 03:59.114
No. No. No, no, no.

04:00.115 --> 04:01.283
Whoa!

04:01.283 --> 04:03.702
Whoa!

04:14.505 --> 04:16.006
What?

04:24.598 --> 04:25.766
Uh-oh.

04:29.353 --> 04:31.855
How's it going?

04:33.607 --> 04:34.525
Oh, my gosh!

04:34.525 --> 04:36.610
Are you okay?
Did you fall through that vent?

04:36.610 --> 04:38.237
Damian, you could've
gotten hurt.

04:38.237 --> 04:39.571
You shouldn't play
with the cat.

04:39.571 --> 04:41.490
You could've gotten
scratched, or worse!

04:41.490 --> 04:42.658
You could've gotten
a brain parasite

04:42.658 --> 04:44.076
from its fecal matter.

04:46.495 --> 04:47.663
A boo-boo!

04:48.247 --> 04:49.373
Aw, Dad!

04:49.373 --> 04:50.749
Quit worrying so much.

04:50.749 --> 04:52.126
I'm totally fine.

04:52.126 --> 04:54.086
The HVAC unit broke
my fall, see?

04:58.841 --> 04:59.758
Yeah.

05:00.426 --> 05:03.762
Damian, what have we said
about being more careful

05:03.762 --> 05:06.390
and less destructive when
you're playing superhero?

05:06.390 --> 05:08.475
I'm not playing, Dad.
I'm training.

05:08.475 --> 05:10.602
To be a real hero. Like you.

05:11.186 --> 05:13.939
Picture it. You and me
fighting back to back.

05:13.939 --> 05:15.941
Fearless defenders
of the night.

05:15.941 --> 05:18.485
Protecting the weak.
Punishing the wicked.

05:18.485 --> 05:20.487
Crime doesn't stand a chance.

05:21.155 --> 05:22.406
Uh-huh. And I've told you,

05:22.406 --> 05:24.450
you're not ready
for that kind of stuff.

05:24.450 --> 05:25.492
Because being
a superhero takes...

05:25.492 --> 05:28.871
 Focus,
responsibility and sacrifice.

05:28.871 --> 05:30.164
I know. I know.

05:30.164 --> 05:32.583
Not to mention a pretty
high pain threshold.

05:32.583 --> 05:34.293
You know how many ribs
I've broken?

05:34.293 --> 05:35.377
All of them.

05:36.670 --> 05:39.548
Cool! I want to break
all of my ribs, too.

05:39.548 --> 05:40.841
Come on, kiddo.

05:40.841 --> 05:42.593
Now look, even if I thought
you were ready

05:42.593 --> 05:44.803
to be a crime fighter,
which I don't,

05:44.803 --> 05:47.389
there isn't any crime
left in Gotham to fight.

05:47.389 --> 05:48.807
What do you mean?

05:48.807 --> 05:51.351
Damian? The day I found out
I was going to be a dad

05:51.351 --> 05:53.312
was the happiest day
I've had since...

05:54.271 --> 05:55.939
Well, a long time.

05:55.939 --> 05:58.108
It's like in one instant,
the only thing that mattered

05:58.108 --> 06:00.027
was protecting you
from ever getting hurt.

06:00.736 --> 06:02.237
So before you were born,

06:02.237 --> 06:04.490
I worked overtime
to make Gotham safe.

06:26.428 --> 06:27.763
What was that?

06:34.520 --> 06:35.521
<i>- In breaking news,</i>

06:35.521 --> 06:37.147
<i>all of Gotham City's
supervillains</i>

06:37.147 --> 06:39.149
<i>are now either behind bars</i>

06:39.149 --> 06:41.026
<i>or have been forced
into retirement.</i>

06:41.026 --> 06:44.279
<i>Gotham is officially
90 days crime free</i>

06:44.279 --> 06:46.865
<i>as Batman continues
to clean it up.</i>

06:46.865 --> 06:48.617
<i>Gotham City just voted</i>

06:48.617 --> 06:50.828
<i>the safest place
on planet Earth.</i>

06:53.705 --> 06:56.125
There is no more crime
in Gotham.

06:57.126 --> 06:58.710
So enjoy being a kid.

06:58.710 --> 07:00.504
But I don't wanna be
just a kid.

07:00.504 --> 07:03.132
Whoa! You are way more
than just a kid.

07:03.715 --> 07:04.633
You're "my" kid.

07:05.134 --> 07:07.052
- And that's the best kind.

07:09.596 --> 07:12.766
Wait, Dad, what were you doing
down in the basement anyway?

07:12.766 --> 07:14.893
Me? Oh, uh, I don't know.

07:14.893 --> 07:16.228
Maybe I was, uh...

07:16.228 --> 07:18.856
...wrapping
someone's Christmas present.

07:18.856 --> 07:20.440
- Yes! What is it?

07:20.440 --> 07:22.734
Tell me. Tell me. Tell me.
Tell me. Tell me.

07:22.734 --> 07:24.528
Sorry, sport. Bedtime.

07:24.528 --> 07:26.071
Can I at least get a hint?

07:26.071 --> 07:29.783
Let's just say it's something
no future superhero

07:29.783 --> 07:31.285
should be without.

07:31.285 --> 07:33.287
- Is it a Bat-grappling gun?
- Nope.

07:33.287 --> 07:36.582
- Razor-lined Bat-gauntlets.
- Good gravy. No!

07:36.582 --> 07:38.625
- Bat-ice skates?
- Skates?

07:38.625 --> 07:40.294
Now, that's just silly.

07:41.545 --> 07:43.297
Is it
a Bat-laser torch?

07:43.297 --> 07:44.298
No.

07:48.802 --> 07:50.304
Bat-cryptographer sequencer?

07:50.304 --> 07:52.222
I'm not even sure what that is.

07:52.222 --> 07:54.558
A heat-seeking
Bat-rocket launcher?

07:54.558 --> 07:57.561
Nope. And you guessed
that already. Twice.

07:59.563 --> 08:00.856
Master Wayne,

08:00.856 --> 08:03.025
stop playing with your
blood sausage.

08:03.025 --> 08:05.235
Right, yeah,
totally. Sorry, Alfred.

08:05.235 --> 08:07.988
Now, let's enjoy
the traditional

08:07.988 --> 08:10.365
Christmas Eve
breakfast of my youth.

08:10.365 --> 08:11.575
Best hurry.

08:11.575 --> 08:14.494
If jellied eel sits too
long, it tends to...

08:15.412 --> 08:16.622
congeal.

08:19.833 --> 08:21.084
Mm. Mm.

08:31.220 --> 08:32.137
Mm.

08:32.137 --> 08:34.806
Donut tell anybody.

08:34.806 --> 08:36.850
Kapow!

08:36.850 --> 08:38.227
<i>♪ Da-na-na-na-na-na ♪</i>

08:38.227 --> 08:41.063
And no cowls
at the table.

08:41.063 --> 08:43.607
Aw, come one.
It's Christmas Eve!

08:43.607 --> 08:45.442
Damian, you heard Alfred.

08:53.116 --> 08:54.243
Hmph.

08:56.161 --> 08:57.246
Ah, what the heck?

08:58.580 --> 09:00.249
Here you go, Damian.

09:00.249 --> 09:03.585
Whoa! You mean
I can open it now?

09:03.585 --> 09:05.963
Why not? You get
to stop guessing

09:05.963 --> 09:07.714
and I get to hear myself
think again.

09:07.714 --> 09:09.925
- It's a win-win.
- Mm-hm.

09:09.925 --> 09:11.677
Merry Christmas, kiddo.

09:17.349 --> 09:19.768
My own utility belt!

09:19.768 --> 09:22.813
Yeah, that was
my first utility belt, Damian.

09:22.813 --> 09:25.482
What? No way! Oh, man!
I can't believe it.

09:25.482 --> 09:27.818
This is the best, Dad!
You're the best!

09:27.818 --> 09:29.653
Alfred, isn't Dad the best?

09:29.653 --> 09:32.948
- Oh, my. Yes.

09:32.948 --> 09:34.741
This is indeed exciting.

09:34.741 --> 09:36.576
Oh, what did you put
in the pouches?

09:40.122 --> 09:41.832
That's your Bat-first-aid kit.

09:41.832 --> 09:43.667
Oh, neat.

09:43.667 --> 09:45.252
How about this?

09:45.252 --> 09:47.004
Your Bat-mergency whistle.

09:47.004 --> 09:48.588
Nice.

09:48.588 --> 09:51.550
Which should only be used
in case of a Bat-mergency.

09:53.552 --> 09:56.346
Whoa! A Batarang

10:00.934 --> 10:02.477
- It's foam.

10:03.103 --> 10:05.105
But isn't it supposed to fly
back to me.

10:05.105 --> 10:06.440
So it can poke you in the eye?

10:06.440 --> 10:07.607
I don't think so.

10:07.607 --> 10:09.276
That's a practice Batarang.

10:11.361 --> 10:14.323
Dad, don't get me wrong.
I love this belt.

10:14.323 --> 10:16.616
I mean, I love, love, love it.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.285
But where's the, you know,

10:19.119 --> 10:20.203
cool stuff?

10:20.203 --> 10:21.288
You mean dangerous stuff?

10:21.913 --> 10:23.832
Damian, you'll have
to earn those things
when you're older.

10:23.832 --> 10:25.417
You still have a lot to learn.

10:25.417 --> 10:27.586
Oh, come on, Dad.
I'm not a baby.

10:27.586 --> 10:29.338
Hey, I never said
you were a baby.

10:29.338 --> 10:31.131
<i>Emergency! Call for help.</i>

10:31.131 --> 10:32.799
<i>My precious little baby
is in danger.</i>

10:33.884 --> 10:35.719
I'll re-record that for you.

10:37.137 --> 10:40.307
Damian, this is the first step
toward becoming a superhero.

10:40.307 --> 10:42.434
Believe me,
I agonized for months

10:42.434 --> 10:43.810
over whether you're
ready for even--

10:43.810 --> 10:45.937
- What's that?

10:45.937 --> 10:48.690
- It sounds like the--
- It can't be.

10:48.690 --> 10:50.776
Can't be what?
What can't it be?

10:50.776 --> 10:52.235
The Batphone.

10:53.070 --> 10:55.072
Ooh, wait for me.
I'll put on my belt!

10:55.072 --> 10:56.740
I mean...

10:56.740 --> 10:57.908
Wait for me.

10:57.908 --> 10:59.326
I'll put on my belt.

11:07.501 --> 11:09.419
No one's called
this thing in years.

11:09.419 --> 11:11.713
Crime must be back
in Gotham.

11:11.713 --> 11:13.799
It's a Christmas miracle!

11:14.466 --> 11:16.009
- Hello?

11:16.009 --> 11:17.469
It's the Justice League.

11:17.469 --> 11:19.638
What? Are you serious?

11:19.638 --> 11:20.972
Quick. How's my belt look?

11:20.972 --> 11:23.392
Uh-huh. No, I... I hear you.

11:23.392 --> 11:25.644
A weather anomaly?
In Nova Scotia?

11:25.644 --> 11:27.104
Just let Clark handle it.

11:28.313 --> 11:30.982
It's Christmas Eve.
We all have plans.

11:30.982 --> 11:33.735
No need to send Superman.
We got this.

11:33.735 --> 11:35.153
Sorry, that was Damian.

11:35.153 --> 11:37.114
Yeah, he's eight now.
Crazy, right?

11:37.823 --> 11:39.199
You can't call anyone else?

11:39.199 --> 11:40.367
How about the Twins?

11:40.367 --> 11:42.285
- They're not talking?

11:42.285 --> 11:44.371
Well tell them to activate
their Wonder Twin powers

11:44.371 --> 11:46.331
and form into mature adults.

11:47.791 --> 11:49.084
All right. Fine.

11:49.668 --> 11:50.544
I'll leave in five.

11:52.337 --> 11:54.381
Sorry, Damian. I gotta go.

11:54.381 --> 11:57.551
But I promise I'll be back
before Christmas.

11:57.551 --> 11:59.010
Wait, Dad! Dad! Dad!

11:59.010 --> 12:00.303
Let me come with you. Please!

12:01.012 --> 12:02.180
I don't think so, kiddo.

12:02.180 --> 12:04.683
It could be your Christmas
gift for the next year.

12:04.683 --> 12:06.143
For the next ten years!

12:07.227 --> 12:09.354
I can't risk it.
The answer's no.

12:11.690 --> 12:12.732
Mm.

12:12.732 --> 12:15.277
Good. Now, where's your
emergency contact list?

12:15.277 --> 12:16.319
Actually, never mind.

12:16.319 --> 12:17.904
I printed extra copies
for your belt.

12:21.408 --> 12:22.868
Okay. What do you do

12:22.868 --> 12:24.244
in the event
of a home invasion?

12:24.244 --> 12:25.328
Call the police.

12:25.328 --> 12:26.913
- Mental breakdown?
- Therapist.

12:26.913 --> 12:28.665
A race of giant,
super-intelligent

12:28.665 --> 12:30.208
fungus-beetles attack Gotham?

12:30.208 --> 12:32.210
I don't know.
Call Commissioner Gordon?

12:32.210 --> 12:34.171
Commiss-- What? No!

12:34.171 --> 12:36.047
All he ever does
is pass the buck to me.

12:37.048 --> 12:38.508
I'll be back before
you know it, buddy.

12:39.926 --> 12:42.846
I shall ready the Batjet,
Master Wayne.

12:45.056 --> 12:46.224
Batjet, huh?

13:02.032 --> 13:03.492
You're making record time

13:03.492 --> 13:05.452
for not having done this
in years, Bruce.

13:05.452 --> 13:07.287
Did you program
the coordinates?

13:07.287 --> 13:09.206
And pre-heated
the seat warmer, sir.

13:11.208 --> 13:13.210
Shall I assume

13:13.210 --> 13:16.880
we did not see the Bat-razor
I left on the vanity?

13:16.880 --> 13:18.340
Really? The beard again?

13:19.132 --> 13:22.177
I like it. It totally ups
my intimidation game.

13:24.471 --> 13:27.807
You have donut crumbs
in your intimidation game, sir.

13:29.726 --> 13:30.936
- Hm.

13:30.936 --> 13:32.562
<i>Emergency! Call for help.</i>

13:32.562 --> 13:34.272
<i>My precious little baby
is in danger.</i>

13:34.272 --> 13:35.482
What the...

13:37.567 --> 13:39.402
<i>- Emergency! Call for help.</i>

13:39.402 --> 13:41.238
<i>- My precious little baby...</i>
- Come on.

13:41.238 --> 13:43.114
- Damian!

13:43.114 --> 13:44.574
Wow! Dad!

13:45.617 --> 13:47.619
You look awesome!

13:47.619 --> 13:49.454
Damian, get out of the bag.

13:49.454 --> 13:51.623
Come on, Dad, just let
me come with you.

13:51.623 --> 13:53.875
No. We don't have
time for this.

13:53.875 --> 13:55.460
You won't even know I'm here.

13:55.460 --> 13:56.711
I told you,

13:56.711 --> 13:59.381
- you're not ready.

13:59.381 --> 14:02.050
Ugh! Dad, look how hard
I've been training.

14:02.050 --> 14:03.385
I mean, check out
my rad ninja skills.

14:03.385 --> 14:05.637
-  Get over here. Argh!

14:06.596 --> 14:08.598
Argh! My good hip.

14:08.598 --> 14:10.684
Oh, my gosh! Alfred!
I'm so sorry.

14:11.434 --> 14:14.145
Damian Thomas Wayne!
That is enough!

14:17.857 --> 14:18.692
I just thought

14:19.568 --> 14:20.819
getting your belt meant

14:21.403 --> 14:23.572
that I was ready to be
a superhero like you.

14:24.281 --> 14:25.407
Well, it didn't.

14:26.074 --> 14:27.576
In fact, give me the belt.

14:27.576 --> 14:29.786
You're clearly
not ready for it.

14:29.786 --> 14:31.830
What? Dad, no!

14:32.914 --> 14:33.832
Damian.

14:48.221 --> 14:50.473
Hold on to this
until I get back.

14:52.100 --> 14:53.560
Okay. Now give me a...

14:55.103 --> 14:56.229
goodbye hug?

15:03.820 --> 15:06.239
He'll be fine, sir.
I'll see to that.

15:07.073 --> 15:09.409
I knew he wasn't ready
to have his own belt.

15:10.118 --> 15:12.871
Yes. Well,
I can certainly agree

15:12.871 --> 15:14.873
that "someone" wasn't ready.

15:18.835 --> 15:20.420
I gotta get going, Alfred.

15:31.097 --> 15:32.891
Godspeed, sir.

15:52.410 --> 15:53.745
Come along, Damian.

15:54.329 --> 15:57.290
I've got just the thing
to lift your spirits.

15:57.290 --> 16:00.710
A steaming mug of my
world-famous hot cocoa.

16:00.710 --> 16:02.796
With extra marshmallows.

16:03.421 --> 16:06.049
Thanks, but coco's
kinda kid stuff.

16:06.049 --> 16:07.425
"Kid stuff?"

16:07.425 --> 16:09.719
Oh, your father
would disagree.

16:09.719 --> 16:12.847
I once saw him drink
an entire gallon
in one sitting.

16:12.847 --> 16:14.182
You did not.

16:14.182 --> 16:16.017
Did so.
And he had quite

16:16.017 --> 16:17.769
the swollen stomach
that evening.

16:17.769 --> 16:21.064
Why I had to take
the Batsuit out
an entire two inches

16:21.064 --> 16:22.774
before he could even
go out on patrol.

16:43.837 --> 16:46.089
This is so unfair, Selina.

16:49.509 --> 16:51.344
You're right. I can't give up.

16:51.344 --> 16:54.305
I'll work even harder
to prove I'm ready
to be Batman.

16:55.223 --> 16:56.808
And you know what that means?

16:57.517 --> 16:59.769
Time for some extreme training.

17:03.440 --> 17:06.025
Unsupervised
extreme training.

17:10.864 --> 17:12.615
I don't know, Alfred.

17:12.615 --> 17:15.285
Do you really think
a steaming mug

17:15.285 --> 17:17.287
of your world-famous
hot cocoa

17:17.287 --> 17:19.706
with extra marshmallows
could help?

17:19.706 --> 17:22.041
Why I'm certain of it, sir.

17:22.041 --> 17:24.711
Unless it's too much trouble.

17:24.711 --> 17:26.504
Nonsense. Coming up.

17:31.092 --> 17:34.179
All right, Pennyworth,
time to deliver your A-game.

17:45.565 --> 17:48.318
Aw, man!

18:00.079 --> 18:01.164
Hm.

18:02.665 --> 18:03.583
Hmph.

18:21.226 --> 18:24.229
And now
the piece de resistance.

18:26.064 --> 18:29.150
Good heavens!
Out of marshmallows?

18:29.150 --> 18:30.485
- What?

18:30.485 --> 18:32.237
How did that happen?

18:33.154 --> 18:35.490
This is catastrophic.

18:35.490 --> 18:36.908
That's okay.

18:36.908 --> 18:38.159
After all, it's...

18:38.159 --> 18:40.453
it's only cocoa
without marshmallows.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.581
It's not like
it's Christmas Eve

18:43.581 --> 18:44.707
without my...

18:44.707 --> 18:46.125
...dad.

18:55.468 --> 18:57.095
Fear not.

18:57.095 --> 18:59.597
I shall return
before your cocoa

18:59.597 --> 19:01.349
even has a chance to cool.

